        "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-10 07:20:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nHi James,\n\nAccording to https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/PUB/Coding+Guidelines , we should use tabs instead of spaces for indentation.\n\nIn addition, the patch needs be run through build/checkpatch.pl to catch problems like this. Installing the git prepare-commit-msg hook does this automatically at commit time:\n\nln -sf ../../build/commit-msg .git/hooks/\n\nln -sf ../../build/prepare-commit-msg .git/hooks/",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
